@Dibbyo456 Thanks for your time and effort on this! It seems this fix works because `/me/drive` [automatically provisions](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/onedrive/developer/rest-api/api/drive_get?view=odsp-graph-online#get-current-users-onedrive) the user's OneDrive:

> If a user's OneDrive is not provisioned but the user has a license to use OneDrive, this request will automatically provision the user's drive, when using delegated authentication.

Would you like to open a PR for this?

@Cnly sorry for removing the previous comment I accidentally posted some personal info which I needed to remove.

> Would you like to open a PR for this?

Well I can remove `s` but I don't think that is sufficient, because it may need some function to catch the `id`, I don't know golang (although I am learning).

