**Original comment:** @ncw I finally debugged it.

When we config rclone and choose `OneDrive Personal or Business`, rclone send request to `/me/drives` endpoint. However the `/me/drives` endpoint returns the following response:

```
{
    "@odata.context": "https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/$metadata#drives",
    "value": [
        {
            "createdDateTime": "2019-07-27T09:07:55Z",
            "description": "Use this Picture Library to store logos for Organizations.",
            "id": "{redacted}",
            "lastModifiedDateTime": "2019-07-27T09:07:55Z",
            "name": "Organization Logos",
            "webUrl": "{redacted}",
            "driveType": "documentLibrary",
            "createdBy": {
                "user": {
                    "displayName": "System Account"
                }
            },
            "quota": {
                "deleted": 0,
                "remaining": 0,
                "total": 0,
                "used": 0
            }
        },
        {
            "createdDateTime": "2019-07-27T09:07:55Z",
            "description": "Profile Pictures for all users will be stored here.",
            "id": "{redacted}",
            "lastModifiedDateTime": "2020-03-17T21:13:25Z",
            "name": "User Photos",
            "webUrl": "{redacted}",
            "driveType": "documentLibrary",
            "createdBy": {
                "user": {
                    "displayName": "System Account"
                }
            },
            "quota": {
                "deleted": 0,
                "remaining": 0,
                "total": 0,
                "used": 0
            }
        }
    ]
}
```
As you can see the actual drive information (documents root) isn't there.

**How to Fix**:

To fix the issue we need to call `/me/drive` instead of `/me/drives` (Note: there is no `s`)

Here is the response if we call `/me/drive` endpoint:

```
{
    "@odata.context": "https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/$metadata#drives/$entity",
    "createdDateTime": "2020-03-07T20:08:42Z",
    "description": "",
    "id": "{redacted}",
    "lastModifiedDateTime": "2020-03-20T07:43:45Z",
    "name": "OneDrive",
    "webUrl": "https://{redacted}-my.sharepoint.com/personal/{redacted}/Documents",
    "driveType": "business",
    "createdBy": {
        "user": {
            "displayName": "System Account"
        }
    },
    "lastModifiedBy": {
        "user": {
            "email": "{redacted}",
            "id": "{redacted}",
            "displayName": "{redacted}"
        }
    },
    "owner": {
        "user": {
            "email": "{redacted}",
            "id": "{redacted}",
            "displayName": "{redacted}"
        }
    },
    "quota": {
        "deleted": 0,
        "remaining": 5497557365266,
        "state": "normal",
        "total": 5497558138880,
        "used": 0
    }
}
```
In short: all we need is remove the `s` from [Line 129](https://github.com/rclone/rclone/blob/master/backend/onedrive/onedrive.go#L129).
